    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so the mechanosensors are basically triggered by the physical strain... it's hard for me to visualize it. can you give me an analogy of how those proteins actually respond to the stress so it's easier to understand?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Imagine your muscle fiber is a heavily loaded bridge under stress. The mechanosensors are like the stress gauges bolted onto the beams of that bridge. When the load (tension) exceeds a certain threshold, these gauges don't just record the data; they send an immediate, urgent alert signal. This alert signal then powers up the construction crew—the mTOR pathway—to start reinforcing the bridge structure with stronger, new materials (protein synthesis).",
      "source": "target",
